The Nernst potential (Eq. 5) of a SOFC is the open-circuit voltage (OCV) assuming complete reversibility of all electrochemical processes within the cell. When drawing current from the SOFC, the cell potential will drop due to overpotential losses [149]. The voltaic efficiency is the ratio between the output cell potential and the Nernst potential (Eq. 9) [165].9\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
