The ohmic overpotential (ηohm) is the potential required to overcome the internal resistance of the cell [169]. It is quantified by Ohm’s law where i is the operating current density of the cell, Rp is polarization the resistance of the electrodes, and Rs is the series resistance at the electrolyte (Eq. 11) [149].11\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
